### **1. Researcher Phase: Technology Selection**

Based on your stack (Go 1.21+, React 18, Postgres, Redis), the following libraries are selected for optimal stability and performance:

| Component | Selection | Rationale |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Claude SDK** | `github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go` | Official SDK. Strongly typed, supports latest models (Claude 3.5 Sonnet/Opus). |
| **Orchestration** | `github.com/hibiken/asynq` | Redis-backed, high-performance task queue. Supports retries, scheduling, and distinct queues. |
| **Config View** | `@rjsf/core` + `@rjsf/validator-ajv8` | Generates dynamic React forms from JSON Schema. Perfect for editing complex LLM configs. |
| **DB Access** | `pgx/v5` + `sqlc` (or GORM) | `pgx` for performance. We will use raw SQL/structs here for clarity. |

